{
  "texts": [
    "A soft (x) = σ(W • f (x))(3)where σ(•) denotes sigmoid activation constraining outputs to [0,1], W is a learnable weight matrix, and f (x) represents feature activations at spatial location x.",
    "The computed attention mask A soft exhibits higher values for tumor regions and lower values for background, enabling adaptive feature recalibration:f attended (x) = A soft (x) ⊙ f (x)(4)where ⊙ denotes element-wise multiplication.",
    "This mechanism effectively reweights spatial locations, directing network focus toward clinically informative tumor regions while suppressing irrelevant background noise.",
    "Sigmoid(Q) = 1 1 + exp(-Q) (5)Binary cross-entropy loss optimizes the segmentation network:L BCE = - 1 N N i=1 [y i log(p i) + (1 -y i) log(1 -p i)](6)where N denotes total voxel count, y i ∈ {0, 1} is ground truth label, and p i is model prediction.",
    "This logarithmic formulation applies higher penalty to confident misclassifications, naturally addressing class imbalance (background voxels vastly outnumber tumor voxels).The segmentation network is trained using the Adam optimizer with learning rate α = 0.001, batch size 16, and up to 100 epochs."
  ]
}